headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 24 points in his return from an eight-game absence with an illness, getting 14 in the fourth quarter to help the Boston Celtics hold off the Brooklyn Nets 115-113 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 24 in his return to help the Celtics hold on to beat the Nets 115-113

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 48 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Detroit Pistons 113-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 48 points and Thunder hold off Pistons 113-107

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 28 points and the Houston Rockets extended their winning streak to six straight games with a 117-114 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 28 and the Rockets down the Bulls 117-114

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 31 points, Desmond Bane added 22 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists as the Memphis Grizzlies led from start to finish in a 125-91 victory over the Miami Heat on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Bane lead Grizzlies to 125-91 victory over Miami, Heat's 7th straight loss

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists before fouling out and the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Indiana Pacers 126-119 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks take big lead and then hang on down the stretch to beat Pacers 126-119

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell scored 22 points and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 119-115 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell scores 22 points and Spurs hold off Pelicans, who were without Williamson

events.name: New York Knicks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 28 points, seven rebounds and five assists two days after becoming the first player in NBA history with 4,000 3-pointers and a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry has 28 points, Kerr becomes Warriors' regular-season victory leader in 97-94 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole hit a 3-pointer with 2.1 seconds left to give the Washington Wizards a 126-123 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole's 3-pointer with 2.1 seconds left gives Wizards a 126-123 win over the Nuggets
